The paper focuses on deep-networks-based hashing for large-scale image retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and deep learning techniques, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel combination strategy for fusing low-level features, which involves making decisions based on consensus, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
